Control

Class KeyBoardHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • Control.KeyBoardHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.KeyListener, java.util.EventListener

    public class KeyBoardHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.event.KeyListener
    This class is used as a keyListener to handle the control of the player object. It takes as an argument a reference to an object of type "Player" which is the object wanted to be controlled
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    FarisAlasmary
    See Also:
    Player

      • KeyBoardHandler

        public KeyBoardHandler(Player player,
               int velocity,
               java.awt.Dimension screenSize)
        Constructs a keyboard handler to be used as a "KeyListener" for another class
        Parameters:
        player - is the object wanted to be controlled
        velocity - the velocity that is going to be used as the speed of the player
        screenSize - is the size of the screen to keep the player inside the screen
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if there is no player OR no screenSize
